body_html: I'd ideally like to get GCS / AWS / etc. support in TensorBoard, most of the time, without having to import tensorflow. I know with Linux I can invoke a gsutil subprocess. Is there something like that on Windows? How hard could it be?

body: I'd ideally like to get GCS / AWS / etc. support in TensorBoard, most of the time, without having to `import tensorflow`. I know with Linux I can invoke a `gsutil` subprocess. Is there something like that on Windows? How hard could it be?
